case_circumstances: The decedent reportedly left a bar in Immokalee with a man in order to go to Fort Myers. On the way, the man stopped the vehicle to let the decedent out to urinate. At this time, the man beat the decedent to death. In January of 1987, the man confessed to the crime and in 1991 was sentenced for the crime. He did not know the decedent's name. The decedent is believed to be a migrant farm worker.
case_head_hair: Medium length black hair with minimal graying
case_clothing_on_body: Red and blue striped shirt, off-white pants, work boots, brown socks, and jockey-type under shorts.
case_other_items_with_body: Blue and white baseball cap, $10.00, a men's "Timex" watch, 1 pack of Marlboro cigarettes, a Bic lighter, a blue hankerchief, and an empty key case
